# PRAXIS Dashboard & Human Gate UI Guidelines (Monica's Pillar)

Architecture source of truth: `docs/plans/PRAXIS_Project_Plan.html`.  
Pillar docs: `docs/monica/` (architecture, plan, as-built wireframes).

## Component Structure
- Human gate states: proposed → suggested → active with clear visual transitions and provenance display on every item.
- Use consistent confidence/credibility score components (frequency, recency, breadth indicators) with tooltips explaining rationale.
- Contradiction resolution UI: side-by-side comparison cards with resolution actions that update state and trigger backend approval flow.

## State & Data Flow
- Dashboard shell + candidate list on Day 2; detail views wired by Day 3.
- All approval actions (promote, reject, resolve) must show audit trail and link to originating JSONL lines.
- Integrate with backend API on Days 6-7; handle loading/error states with provenance context preserved.

## Demo & Accessibility
- Ensure flows are keyboard-accessible and screen-reader friendly for live demo on Days 9-10.
- Polish edge cases (Day 8) so review experience feels effortless and trustworthy.
- Coordinate with Dominic on eval metrics visualization embedding if needed.

These patterns ensure the "human in the loop" pillar is interview-ready and supports ≥50% correction reduction narrative.
